        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cylinder is leaking</strong><p>A leaking cylinder must be replaced. A drip from a valve or fitting can sometimes be resolved without replacing the cylinder. We diagnose on the visit before quoting any work.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Hot water takes more than 45 minutes to reheat</strong><p>Failing immersion element, corroded heat exchanger coil or faulty thermostat. We diagnose the cause and give you an honest assessment before recommending repair or replacement.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cylinder is over 20 years old</strong><p>Most hot water cylinders have a working life of 15 to 25 years. A Formby cylinder over 20 years old is at increasing risk of failure. Proactive replacement from £600 is considerably cheaper than emergency water damage repair.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Poor pressure throughout a multi-bathroom property</strong><p>A vented gravity-fed system cannot deliver mains-pressure hot water simultaneously to multiple bathrooms. Upgrading to an unvented cylinder from £900 resolves this permanently.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Banging or kettling from the cylinder or pipework</strong><p>Limescale build-up on the immersion element or heat exchanger, or air in the system. Often resolved with element replacement. We assess on the visit before recommending what is needed.</p></div></div>
